    About

    Description

    Leonardo di ser Piero da Vinci was an Italian polymath of the High Renaissance who was active as a painter, draughtsman, engineer, scientist, theorist, sculptor, and architect. Wikipedia
    Born: April 15, 1452, Anchiano, Italy
    Died: May 2, 1519 (age 67 years), Château du Clos Lucé, Amboise, France
    Place of burial: Chapel of Saint-Hubert, Amboise, France
    Periods: Renaissance, Italian Renaissance, High Renaissance
    Influenced by: Andrea del Verrocchio, Lorenzo de' Medici, John Argyropoulos
    Influenced: Michelangelo, Raphael, Niccolo Machiavelli, MORE
    On view: Royal Collection Trust, Museo Galileo, Louvre Museum, MORE
